OL,3,CLucy Letby's father 'wanted dismissal
OL,4,Cof two consultants who raised concerns'
OL,6,F"These were however exceptional
OL,7,Fcircumstances and I felt I needed to
OL,8,Fstep in and support other members of
OL,9,Fstaff who were struggling with the
OL,10,Famount of pressure being exerted."
OL,12,FChief executive Tony Chambers went on
OL,13,Fto ask the consultants to apologise to
OL,14,FLetby for the alleged derogatory
OL,15,Fremarks and days later the nurse
OL,16,Femailed her colleagues to say she
OL,17,Fwould be returning to the unit after
OL,18,Fshe had been "fully exonerated" of
OL,19,Fallegations made against her.
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@bO]zD@NOUzD@_O]
